  "rollout_plan_displayname": "(RARE) Experiment users ramp up over time",
  "motivation": "Currently, Chromium only extracts the charset parameter from data URLs and\ndiscards other MIME type parameters. Per the Fetch Standard, data URL MIME\ntype parameters should be preserved in the Content-Type header.\n\nFor example:\n- data:text/plain;a=b,X should return Content-Type: text/plain;a=b\n- data:;charset=\" x\",X should return Content-Type: text/plain;charset=\" x\"\n\nThis change brings Chromium into compliance with the Fetch Standard and\nimproves web compatibility with other browsers.\n\nSpec: https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#data-url-processor",
